Project Overview
The Kirana+ chatbot is designed to facilitate seamless communication between local stores and consumers, enabling easy order placements and registrations. The chatbot leverages IBM Watson Assistant for natural language processing and understanding.

Getting Started
To get a local copy of the repository and start training the chatbot, follow the steps below.

Prerequisites
An IBM Cloud account. Sign up here if you don't have one.
Node.js installed on your local machine.
IBM Watson SDK for Node.js, which can be installed via npm.

Installation
Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/your-username/kirana-plus-chatbot.git
cd kirana-plus-chatbot

Install required dependencies:
npm install

Set up IBM Watson Assistant:

Create an IBM Watson Assistant service instance on IBM Cloud.
Note down the API Key, URL, and Workspace ID.

Configure environment variables:

Rename .env.example to .env and add your credentials:
WATSON_ASSISTANT_APIKEY=your_api_key
WATSON_ASSISTANT_URL=your_service_url
WATSON_ASSISTANT_WORKSPACE_ID=your_workspace_id

Training the Chatbot
Prepare training data:

Training data should be in a JSON format compatible with IBM Watson Assistant. For reference, see the Watson Assistant API Documentation.
Upload the training data:

Use the Watson Assistant web interface or the API to upload your training data.

Run the training script:
npm run train

Usage
Once trained, the chatbot can be tested using the IBM Watson Assistant interface or via the command line:
npm run start

